  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Wellbeing of Crisis-Affected Populations in Displacement-Affected Locations Is Strengthened through Site Management Support, Including Site Planning &amp; Development, Coordination &amp; Information Management, Community Participation and Capacity Building</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Ethiopia the internal displacement and humanitarian needs are mainly derived by the ongoing conflicts and floods in the country. The primary drivers of displacement were conflict (62%), followed by drought (17%), flash floods (9%) and seasonal floods (6%). The ongoing conflicts, climate shocks and displacements continue to pose serious protection concerns for the affected population. The majority of the displaced population live-in collective sites or in spontaneous settlements where they have limited access to essential services, dignified and safe living conditions and lack necessary resources to sustain their families and communities. This project aims to increase the wellbeing of crisis-affected populations in displacement-affected locations through Site Management Support (SMS) / Camp Coordination and Camp management (CCCM), including site planning and development, coordination and information management, community participation and capacity building.</narrative>
  </description>
